Package de.fu.scheduler.model.data

Class Summary
Configuration  
CourseElementInstance  
Day Day has a name, for instance "Monday".
ElementInstancePreferredRoom ElementInstancePreferredRoom is the bridge class for the many-to-many relation between CourseElementInstance and Room.
ElementInstancePreferredTimeSlot ElementInstancePreferredTimeSlot is the bridge class for the many-to-many relation between CourseElementInstance and TimeSlot.
ElementInstanceRequiredFeature ElementInstanceRequiredFEature is the bridge class for the many-to-many relation between CourseElementInstance and Feature.
Feature Feature represents the fulfillment respectively requirements of soft constraints and hard constraints.
Person Person is a lecturer and has the preferred time slots in order to check a soft constraint.
PersonPreferredTimeSlot PersonPreferredTimeSlot is the bridge class for the many-to-many relation between Person and TimeSlot.
ProposedScheduling ProposedScheduling is the allocation of a CourseElementInstance to a Room and a TimeSlot in a Schedule that is not finished.
Room Room has a list of provided features to fulfill hard constraints and soft constraints.
RoomPreferresTimeSlot RoomPreferresTimeSlot is the bridge class for the many-to-many relation between Room and TimeSlot.
RoomProvidedFeature RoomProvidedFeature is the bridge class for the many-to-many relation between Room and Feature.
TimeSlot TimeSlot is the representation of discrete time units of a day.
